contentrichtext.text: '''UST''' is a [[three letter acronym]] that may refer to: * [[University of Santo Tomas]] in Manila, Philippines ** [[UST Growling Tigers]], men's varsity team * [[Hong Kong University of Science and Technology]] (HKUST) * [[Equatorial Guinea Workers' Union]] * [[Northeast Florida Regional Airport]] in St. Augustine, Florida (IATA Airport Code UST) * [[Underground storage tank]] * [[Union of Trade Unions of Chad]] (Union des Syndicats du Tchad) * [[Universal Standard Time]] * Universal System Tubeless, a tubeless bicycle tire system developed by [[Mavic]] * [[University of St. Thomas (Texas)]] in Houston * [[University of St. Thomas (Minnesota)]] in Twin Cities * [[University of Science and Technology (disambiguation)]], universities focus on science and technology * [[University of Science and Technology (South Korea)]], a group of public universities and research institutions * [[Tiraspol State University]] in Moldova * [[Sexual_tension|Unresolved Sexual Tension]], the acronym originating with fans of [[The X-Files]] ** [[UST_(Film)| ''UST'']] (2013), film. * [[Unsepttrium]] (Ust), the predicted last electrically neutral chemical element, with an [[atomic number]] of 173 * [[U.S. Smokeless Tobacco Company]], a subsidiary of UST Inc. * ''[[United States of Tara]]'', an American comedy-drama television series * [[Ustream]] website * .ust, file extension for plain-text [[Utau]] voice sequence files * [[Uniform Spanning Tree]], a mathematical concept; a randomly (uniformly) chosen spanning tree of a graph * [[United States Treasury]] Department of the Treasury of the United States ==See also== * [[Qala Wust]], also known as Åªst, a village in the Wakhan region of Badakhshan Province, Afghanistan {{disambig}}
